    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"files-buffers-windows-splits-and-tabs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#files-buffers-windows-splits-and-tabs\" aria-label=\"files buffers windows splits and tabs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Files, Buffers, Windows, Splits, and Tabs</h2>\n<p>We all know what files are (or so you think <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VVdmmN0su6E\">LiveOverflow's Video on\nFiles</a>) but there is a bit more\nwhen it comes to how vim handles them.</p>\n<h3 id=\"buffer\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#buffer\" aria-label=\"buffer permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Buffer</h3>\n<p>A buffer contains the text of the file and is what you edit.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">:h buffer</code></p>\n<h3 id=\"window\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#window\" aria-label=\"window permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Window</h3>\n<p>Contains a buffer to display.  Windows can be closed but the underlying buffer\ncan remain in memory.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">:h window</code></p>\n<h3 id=\"tabs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tabs\" aria-label=\"tabs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tabs</h3>\n<p>A tab is like another viewport.  You can have many windows|splits open per tab.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">:h tab</code></p>\n<h3 id=\"splits\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#splits\" aria-label=\"splits permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Splits</h3>\n<p>A split simply refers to splitting the viewport in N sections (various sizing\nand orientations available) to display windows.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">:h split</code></p>\n<h2 id=\"other-terminology\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#other-terminology\" aria-label=\"other terminology permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other Terminology</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/14747/view-and-terms.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 48.50000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Terms\"\n        title=\"Terms\"\n        src=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/5a190/view-and-terms.png\"\n        srcset=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/772e8/view-and-terms.png 200w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/e17e5/view-and-terms.png 400w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/5a190/view-and-terms.png 800w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/c1b63/view-and-terms.png 1200w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/29007/view-and-terms.png 1600w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/9390fd226cb749f49156af1e290e0c2c/14747/view-and-terms.png 1914w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"help-menu\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#help-menu\" aria-label=\"help menu permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Help Menu</h2>\n<p>Help menu can be accessed by typing <code class=\"language-text\">:h&lt;enter></code>.  There is <em>so much\ndocumentation</em>, that is pretty good, available.  If you find yourself lost,\nRTFM (at least that is what they tell me).</p>\n<h2 id=\"motion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#motion\" aria-label=\"motion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Motion</h2>\n<p>A command that moves the cursor (taken straight from the help docs, <code class=\"language-text\">:h motion</code>).</p>\n<h2 id=\"abbreviations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#abbreviations\" aria-label=\"abbreviations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Abbreviations</h2>\n<p>Ctrl+a will be abbreviated <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;C-a></code>.  This is also how its referenced in VimL,\nVim's editor language.</p>\n<p>Enter will often be abbr as <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;CR></code></p>\n<p>Tab, Escape, and space will be <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;tab></code>, <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;esc></code>, <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;space></code></p>\n<p>When you see something that starts with a <code class=\"language-text\">:</code> that means it will execute a command.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/terms","title":"The Terminology","order":"2A","section":"Introduction","description":"This goes over some basic vocabulary that will be used"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"53A","path":"/pit-stop","title":"Pit Stop"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"54A","path":"/adv-motions","title":"Advanced Motions"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"50A","path":"/search-and-replace","title":"Search And Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"51A","path":"/macros","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"52A","path":"/registers","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3A","path":"/are-you-ready","title":"Are You Ready?"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"5A","path":"/basic-usage","title":"Using Vim"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"10A","path":"/color-my-pencils","title":"Color My Pencils"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"69A","path":"/exercise-0","title":"hjkl-x"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"70A","path":"/exercise-1","title":"dyp"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"71A","path":"/exercise-2","title":"insert"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"72A","path":"/exercise-3","title":"Search and Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"73A","path":"/exercise-4","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"74A","path":"/exercise-5","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"75A","path":"/exercise-6","title":"Advanced Motions"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"15A","path":"/files-e","title":"Files and Navigations - Edit"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"11A","path":"/files","title":"Files and Navigations"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"16A","path":"/files-marks","title":"Files and Navigations - Marks"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"12A","path":"/files-netrw","title":"Files and Navigations - NetRW"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"17A","path":"/files-recap","title":"Files and Navigations - Recap"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"13A","path":"/files-remaps-1","title":"Files and Navigations - Remaps part 1"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"14A","path":"/files-remaps-2","title":"Files and Navigations - Remaps part 2"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"60A","path":"/your-first-plugin","title":"First Plugin"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"1A","path":"/intro","title":"Introduction"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"20A","path":"/pit-stop","title":"Pit Stop"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"4A","path":"/opening-vim","title":"Opening Vim"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"30A","path":"/plugins","title":"Plugins"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"40A","path":"/quickfix","title":"Quickfix In